*Current behavior*:

Sourcetree uses this sequence to pull from repo:

{code}
hg incoming --bundle X
hg pull -u X
{code}

However, this does not update largefiles. as it has a bug according to the link below:

- http://bz.selenic.com/show_bug.cgi?id=4467

*Workround*:

These options should work fine:

{code}
hg incoming --bundle X
hg pull X
hg update
{code}

or
{code}
hg incoming --bundle X
hg ubundle -u X
{code}

or
{code}
hg incoming --bundle X
hg unbundle X
hg update
{code}

h4. Steps to reproduce
# Create account {{test@test.com}} in Stash
# Connect to Stash from SourceTree using {{test@test.com}}
# Check Stash access logs

h4. Expected response
SourceTree lists out the user repository by using {{GET /rest/api/1.0/users/test_test.com/repos HTTP/1.1}}

h4. Actual response
The user repositories are not listed because the GET request is incorrect {{GET /rest/api/1.0/users/test@test.com/repos HTTP/1.1}}

h4. Analysis
Username: {{test@test.com}}
User Slug in Stash: {{test_test.com}}
The request should be done using the User slug instead of the User Name
